  "riddle": "1. A place where districts number their communities — how many communes does this locality hold? \n\n2. Scale the heights where this district lies — what is its elevation, in meters, above the sea?\n\n3. Nearby greens lie waiting; how many parks can one find within reach of this district?\n\n4. Take the elevation from clue 2 and the park count from clue 3 — what is the absolute difference between these two values?\n\n5. From where you stand, reflect on a broader landscape — how many municipalities mark their presence in the nation as of 2002?\n\n6. Seek a page about urban spaces divided into quarters; what is the total count of languages spoken there?\n\n7. A sacred place within the community holds deep meaning. What religious affiliation does this mosque embrace?\n\n8. Look closely at the name stumbled upon in clue 7: how many vowels lie hidden within its letters?\n\n9. Now, turn your gaze to the population of the vast land known as Algeria — what figure defines its people?\n\n10. Lastly, compute the expression: take the absolute difference between clue 1 and the elevation from clue 2, then reduce it modulo 10. What single digit emerges from this calculation?",
